title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) that should be less prominent.
OB: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 shows obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) along with other class names.
EB: The obfuscated classes should be less prominent in the All types dialog.
SR:
To reproduce the issue in JDK 1.4: 
1. Open the All types dialog in the software. 
2. Observe the presence of obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) in the dialog.
